Jim=97attached is some of the background.

PRISM collects field flow monitoring data from several gravity flow meters =
and rain gauges in the system.
[cid:4ec10a3e-08d9-4b66-badd-1d754b413dc0]


Flow and Rainfall from PRISM are analyzed with Sliicer to disaggregate flow=
 into dry-weather and wet-weather components.
[cid:6723c19d-fbd7-420e-8909-14d208b1db74]

Basin properties are applied to build metrics, such as how much infiltratio=
n do we have in terms of pipe lengths (for example).

To isolate each basin into it's respective influence areas, we subtract ups=
tream flow entering the basin from the total flow leaving the basin. Most o=
f the large flows are metered, but some of the smaller flows we want to imp=
ort from AF.

Currently, we have the ability to create a location in Sliicer and import f=
low from AF as a CSV file. But, we would like the ability to import that in=
formation from an API connection to AF.
[cid:bc00bcf3-6a40-4733-8b73-de96692f67df]

The second part being, we would like to take the analysis from Sliicer and =
export it to PowerBI to build dashboards.


The AF flow is estimated from cycle time in AF
[cid:115a8f91-b606-4087-a173-cb1dc1d61204]

D. Craig Jones, PE

Manager - W/WW Modeling & Analysis

